    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given that the single-condition quasi-static test is conservative relative to in vivo loading rates and that all quantitative acceptance criteria are satisfied with substantial margin. The provenance chain from claim to foundational experimental data and material property databases is documented. The overall credibility evidence supports regulatory submission.",
